ape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/elephants-sri-lanka\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">These are the best places to see Elephants in Sri Lanka<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-1080x703.jpg\" alt=\"National Parks Sri Lanka\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"293\" alt=\"National Parks Sri Lanka\" class=\"wp-image-63895 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-1080x703.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-800x520.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-450x293.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-30x20.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-163x106.jpg 163w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-277x180.jpg 277w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-768x500.jpg 768w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-1024x666.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-1440x937.jpg 1440w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-300x195.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-600x390.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13.jpg 1920w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-30x20.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091608\/sri-lanka-national-parks-13-1080x703.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p><strong>Downsides: <\/strong>It&#x2019;s difficult to see leopards (there is about half the number of leopards that Yala has) and outside of the excellent bird and elephant watching there aren&#x2019;t many other animals to see.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"h-udawalawe-summary\">Udawalawe Summary<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Location:<\/strong> Just inland, to the west of Yala, surrounding the huge Udawalawe reservoir.<\/li><li><strong>Season:<\/strong> Feb to October (dry season). If you&#x2019;re visiting to see migratory birds then visit between October and April. October to January is the best time to see baby elephants, during the rainy season.<\/li><li><strong>Animals:<\/strong> Best for elephants and bird watching.<\/li><li><strong>Price:<\/strong> From 35 USD for a shared jeep to 75 USD for a private tour.<\/li><li><strong>Where to stay:<\/strong> The park is only 1.5 hours drive from <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/hiriketiya-dikwella\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Dikwella<\/a>, a beautiful coastal town in the south of Sri Lanka. Stay at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/dikwella-verse-airbnb\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Verse Collective<\/a>: a trendy collaborative space, popular with digital nomads.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--readmore \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--readmore\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>Read:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/hiriketiya-dikwella\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Dikwella &#x2018;The Surf &amp; Beach Gem of Sri Lanka&#x2019;<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-1080x678.jpg\" alt=\"National Parks Sri Lanka\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"283\" alt=\"National Parks Sri Lanka\" class=\"wp-image-63903 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-1080x678.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-800x503.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-450x283.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-30x19.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-163x102.jpg 163w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-287x180.jpg 287w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-768x482.jpg 768w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-1024x643.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-1440x905.jpg 1440w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-300x188.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-600x377.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17.jpg 1920w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-30x19.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091649\/sri-lanka-national-parks-17-1080x678.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-minerriya\"><strong>Minerriya<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Minnerriya is most famous for the spectacular &#x2018;elephant gathering&#x2019;. During September\/October, the lake dries out, and the elephants gather together around the lake and feed on the grassland. Seeing hundreds of elephants all congregated together in one area is one of the most breathtaking experiences. The lake also attracts an amazing array of birdlife, so it&#x2019;s excellent for bird lovers too.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Downsides:<\/strong> Apart from elephants and birdlife, visitors are unlikely to see the variety of wildlife you would see in other national parks in Sri Lanka.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h4 id=\"h-minerriya-summary\">Minerriya Summary<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Location:<\/strong> North\/Central Sri Lanka. Best to visit from Sigiriya.<\/li><li><strong>Season:<\/strong> July to October (dry season). Visit in September\/October to see the great elephant gathering.<\/li><li><strong>Animals:<\/strong> Best for elephants. However, it is also possible to see two unique species of monkey, the Purple Faced Langur, and Toque Macaque.<\/li><li><strong>Price:<\/strong> Varies. However, it&#x2019;s usually around 40-60 USD for a private tour, including pick up, drop off, and entrance fee.<\/li><li><strong>Where to stay:<\/strong> The park is only 30 mins from <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/pidurangala-rock-sigiriya\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Sigiriya<\/a>. Because of this, it&#x2019;s best to combine a visit to the park with a visit to Lion&#x2019;s rock. See all hotels in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/sigiriya-all\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Sigirya<\/a> or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/dambulla-all\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Dambulla<\/a>.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/07091536\/sri-lanka-national-parks-10-540x810.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\